  "title": "Newtons laws - tension in a heavy hanging rope",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a block hanging from a vertical rope. The rope is attached to a hook on a horizontal ceiling.\" src=\"/images/b1808d45070693d091ef898c1849e263.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block with a weight of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"50 newtons\"><math alttext=\"50 newtons\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>50</mn><mtext> N</mtext></math></span></span> hangs vertically by a rope, with uniform density, attached to a hook as shown. The weight of the rope is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"5 newtons\"><math alttext=\"5 newtons\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>5</mn><mtext> N</mtext></math></span></span>. Which statement best describes the tension in the rope?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The tension in the rope is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"50 newtons\"><math alttext=\"50 newtons\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>50</mn><mtext> N</mtext></math></span></span> at every location along the rope.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The tension in the rope is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"55 newtons\"><math alttext=\"55 newtons\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>55</mn><mtext> N</mtext></math></span></span> at every location the rope.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
